title: For Sale:  Daewoo DH40
postcontent: Here's an unusual pistol -- the Daewoo DH40. This is the .40 S&W version of the K5, the South Korean military's sidearm since 1989. If you know these guns, you know they were marketed in the US as the DP51 and now imported by Lionheart as the LH9. This DH40 has an alloy frame and a steel slide, ambidextrous safety switch, and the unique "triple action" trigger. You can fire it in single action, double action, or a "double action plus" mode where the hammer is down but the trigger pull is very light. This is how the Korean Army carries it. This pistol has some nice touches such as grooves on the front and backstraps and a waved topstrap to reduce glare, just like what you get on the Lionheart. The magazine (one included) holds 11 rounds and the DH40 will take Smith & Wesson 4000 series magazines (so I hear. I have not tried one.) This is one solid gun, and I hate to part with it, but this is my only .40 and I'm trying to cut back on ammo. FTF is fine within 20 miles from Salem/Roanoke or Boones Mill (VA DL and bill of sale required). If you really want me to ship this, you pay the shipping and the fee my FFL charges (no more than $20). For more info on the gun, check here: http://www.thefirearmblog.com/blog/2015/05/21/the-korean-daewoo-precision-industries-dh40/.
